Set The Color Of A Matplotlib Plot

This snippit was written by Chris R. Albon and is part of his collection of well-documented Python snippits. All code is written in Python 3 in iPython notebook and offered under the Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International License.

Import numpy and matplotlib.pyplot

In [2]: 
%matplotlib inline
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

Create some simulated data.

In [3]: 
n = 100
r = 2 * np.random.rand(n)
theta = 2 * np.pi * np.random.rand(n)
area = 200 * r**2 * np.random.rand(n)
colors = theta

Create a scatterplot using the a colormap.

Full list of colormaps: http://wiki.scipy.org/Cookbook/Matplotlib/Show_colormaps

In [6]: 
c = plt.scatter(theta, r, c=colors, s=area, cmap=plt.cm.RdYlGn)
